Class CommandBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Command

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.smartdashboard.SmartDashboardData, edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.smartdashboard.SmartDashboardNamedData
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CommandBase

    public abstract class CommandBase
extends edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Command
    The base for all commands, also the class defining robot hardware/config. All atomic commands should subclass CommandBase. CommandBase stores creates and stores each control system.
    Author:
    Luke Shumaker

      • requires

        protected void requires(edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Subsystem subsystem)
        Description copied from class: edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Command
        This method specifies that the given Subsystem is used by this command. This method is crucial to the functioning of the Command System in general.

        Note that the recommended way to call this method is in the constructor.

      • start

        public void start()
        Description copied from class: edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Command
        Starts up the command. Gets the command ready to start.

        Note that the command will eventually start, however it will not necessarily do so immediately, and may in fact be canceled before initialize is even called.
